content:
Provide Web Forms with Web-to-Case

You are here:

SALESFORCE HELP
DOCS
SERVICE CLOUD
Set up a web form that automatically turns support inquiries into cases.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To set up:

* Set your case submission preferences in Setup.
* Decide which case fields to include in your form.
* Use our handy tool to generate the form in HTML.
* Add the HTML to your website.

When a customer submits the form, they receive an automatic email letting them know you’ve received their request. A case is created in your org to track the request. The case is automatically linked to the relevant contact and account based on the customer’s email address.

You can generate up to 5,000 cases per day, or more if you request a higher limit. You can also add reCAPTCHA v2 to filter out spam cases.

Before setting up your web form with Web-to-Case, complete these steps:

* Turn On and Customize Web-to-Case
* Generate and Test Your Web-to-Case Form
* Prevent Spam Cases with reCAPTCHA

Review guidelines and limits for Web-to-Case.
title: Setting up Web Forms with Web-to-Case in Service Cloud
